      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAGIC MATTEO (2) returned from a break in very good order last start when successful over 1760m at Junee on March 17, getting home by 1.3 metres. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw and his last-start form is good enough to win a race of this calibre. HOOKED ON WINNING NZ (1) finished eighth two runs ago then suffered interference and broke when a long last over 1720m at Dubbo at the latest appearance. No excuses from this more advantageous draw. Won't find this any harder so he can return to form. VALENTINI (10) is right in contention after finishing in the placings for the second time in a row last start, beaten 1.75 metres into third at Junee. No reason why she cannot take this out. HOLME BOY (3) returns to the front row and won the last time he started on that line.",
